<s> For your consideration: Web accessibility: - removing barriers that limit the ability of an individual with a disability or a user of alternative computer access methods to use Web content and Web applications or to participate in their development in a manner one chooses, thereby enhancing ones effectiveness, efficiency and the satisfaction experienced.  </s>
<s> The benefits tend to be more universal facilitating: - the needs of even non-disabled users and developers of websites, and - adherence toorganizational or statutory requirements that might be mandated.  </s>
<s> If this is the first slide,it must define Web accessibility in conceptual terms and relegate words like operable, perceivable, navigable, authoring tools etc to later slides that explain the definition.  </s>
<s> The slides that follow do a splendid job there.  </s>
<s> Also it may be a good idea not to use words like "accessible" (or usable)that are in fact being defined.  </s>
